> Using Eligibility

# Tests: David's test cases converted from davids_tests.csv. Covers basic approval/denial paths with various earned income exclusion combinations (federal, EITC, infrequent, student, IRWE, blind work expenses, self-support plan). All cases use A1E or B1E household type, benefit_year 2026, income_standard $1,845.

## Test: david_001 — Both client ($957.50) and DOL ($957.50) adjusted income well below A1E 2026 standard ($1,845) — approve

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope TestDavid001:
  result scope Eligibility.EligibilityDecision

scope TestDavid001:
  definition result.client_data equals Eligibility.ClientData {
    -- gross_earned_income: $2,000
    -- federal_exclusions: $0
    -- eitc_exclusion: $0
    -- irregular_earned_income: $0
    -- student_earned_income: $0
    -- student_monthly_limit: $0
    -- non_needs_based_unearned_remainder: $20
    -- impairment_work_expenses: $0
    -- blind_work_expenses: $0
    -- self_support_exclusion: $0
    -- household_type: A1E
    -- benefit_year: 2026
  }
  definition result.d_o_l_record equals Eligibility.DOLRecord {
    -- dol_earned_income_available: true
    -- dol_quarterly_earnings: $6,000
    -- gross_earned_income: $2,000
    -- federal_exclusions: $0
    -- eitc_exclusion: $0
    -- irregular_earned_income: $0
    -- student_earned_income: $0
    -- student_monthly_limit: $0
    -- non_needs_based_unearned_remainder: $20
    -- impairment_work_expenses: $0
    -- blind_work_expenses: $0
    -- self_support_exclusion: $0
  }
  assertion (result.eligible = Approve)
  assertion (result.reasons = [])
```

